# XGBoost Model Improvement Plan

This plan outlines the steps to dramatically improve the performance and robustness of the ER wait-time prediction model by introducing standard Machine Learning feature engineering techniques and hyperparameter tuning.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **UI Changes vs Hardcoded Defaults**
> Since we are adding `hospital_name` and `region` as features to the model, the model will require these inputs to make a prediction. 
> - **Option A (No UI Change)**: I can hardcode default values (e.g., `hospital_name="Riverside Medical Center"`, `region="Urban"`) in the backend prediction endpoint. The dashboard UI will not change.
> - **Option B (Update UI)**: I can update the Streamlit Dashboard and the backend API to allow the user to select the Hospital and Region when performing risk assessments.
> 
> **Please let me know which option you prefer!**

## Proposed Changes

### `backend/model.py`

#### [MODIFY] [model.py](file:///d:/Work/Springboard/ANTIGRAVITY-SCRATCH/day2/agy-cli-projects-2/ER-Wait-Time/nurse_staffing_system/backend/model.py)
- Update the `features` list to include `hospital_name` and `region`.
- Introduce a scikit-learn `Pipeline` and `ColumnTransformer`:
  - **One-Hot Encoding**: Apply `OneHotEncoder` to `hospital_name` and `region`.
  - **Cyclical Encoding**: Apply a custom transformation (sine/cosine) to the cyclical time features (`month`, `visithour`, `day_of_week`).
  - **Passthrough**: Keep the remaining numeric features as they are.
- Replace the hardcoded XGBoost parameters with a `RandomizedSearchCV` implementation to search over a grid of hyperparameters (`n_estimators`, `learning_rate`, `max_depth`, `subsample`) using 3-fold cross-validation.
- Update `predict_wait_time` to accept `hospital_name` and `region` as arguments, package them into the dataframe, and pass them through the saved `Pipeline`.

